text: Renée Ganneau (born 12 December 1936) is a French former track and road cyclist. She competed at the 1960 UCI Road World Championships, 1962 UCI Road World Championships, 1963 UCI Road World Championships and 1964 UCI Road World Championships. As a track cyclist she became seven time France national champion between 1960 and 1965 in the sprint event four times, and the individual pursuit three times. == References == == Other websites == * RENEE GANNEAU IN TRAINING FOR WORLD CYCLE CHAMPIONSHIPS - ; 26 AUGUST 1962 Category:1936 births Category:French cyclists Category:Living people
